---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageTitle from "../components/PageTitle.astro";
import { t } from "@catena/i18n";

const locale = "en";
const statusUrl = "https://status.catena.run";
---
<Base
  locale={locale}
  title="Service status"
  description="Real-time status of Catena services (catena.run, the client portal, the docs, the billing API). Uptime probed 24/7 by Gatus, on a host separate from the application server. If the main site goes down, this page stays up."
>
  <PageTitle
    title="Service status"
    intro="Public uptime of Catena services. Refreshed minute-by-minute by Gatus."
  />

  <section class="status-info">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What you see here</h2>
      <p>This page shows real-time status of the services Catena operates for ourselves -- the marketing site (<a href="https://catena.run">catena.run</a>), the docs (<a href="https://docs.catena.run">docs.catena.run</a>), the client portal (<a href="https://app.catena.run">app.catena.run</a>), and the billing API.</p>
      <p>Gatus probes run on a host separate from the one serving the apps, so this page stays consultable even if a primary service goes down. Any outage hitting Catena infrastructure is publicly visible; we can't hide it.</p>
      <p>For clients on a retainer, uptime tracking for your own Catena Suite is in your client portal at <a href="https://app.catena.run">app.catena.run</a> (Monitoring section). SLA thresholds depend on your tier (Small: best-effort; Medium / Large: 99.5%).</p>
      <h2>Gatus dashboard</h2>
      <p class="muted">Embed coming once Gatus is publicly exposed at <code>{statusUrl}</code>. In the meantime, email <a href="mailto:hello@catena.run">hello@catena.run</a> or <a href="/en/contact">book a call</a> if you suspect an outage.</p>
      <div class="placeholder">
        <p class="muted"><strong>Status: in build.</strong> The public Gatus dashboard will be embedded here in the next iteration. The internal Gatus instance is already running and powering operator alerts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .status-info {
    padding: var(--catena-space-16) 0;
  }
  .status-info h2 {
    margin-top: var(--catena-space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--catena-space-3);
  }
  .status-info h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .status-info p {
    line-height: var(--catena-lh-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--catena-space-4);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .placeholder {
    margin-top: var(--catena-space-6);
    padding: var(--catena-space-6);
    border: 1px dashed var(--catena-surface-border);
    border-radius: var(--catena-radius-lg);
    background: var(--catena-surface-bg-muted);
  }
  .placeholder p { margin: 0; }
  code {
    font-family: var(--catena-ff-mono);
    font-size: var(--catena-fs-sm);
    padding: 0 var(--catena-space-1);
    background: var(--catena-surface-bg-muted);
    border-radius: var(--catena-radius-sm);
  }
</style>
